# MY CAREER — HTML to Flutter Conversion Plan

Convert the "MY CAREER" Flutter Roadmap Tracker website (HTML/CSS/JS) into a **pixel-perfect Flutter app** (Web + Mobile) following the AI Constitution rules: Clean Architecture, BLoC/Cubit, GetIt DI, Sealed Classes, Material 3 theme extensible architecture, `const` constructors, and dartdoc.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Single language (English), Theme Extensible (Currently Dark only)** — matching the website's `#08090f` dark palette exactly, but built symmetrically to allow light themes in the future.

---

## 📊 Website Feature Inventory

The source website has **6 pages** and **8 modals**, all using persistence:

| Page | Purpose | Key Features |
|------|---------|-------------|
| 🗺️ **Roadmap** | Flutter learning checklist | 16 sections, ~80+ topics, progress bar, collapsible sections, mastery modal (WHY/HOW/DEEP/TEACH), tags (ADV/NEW/LEAD/ALT) |
| 📚 **Books** | Reading list | CRUD cards with icon, title, author, note, PDF link |
| 💡 **Stand Out** | Career tips | CRUD cards with icon, category, title, body |
| 🔧 **Problems** | Problem log | CRUD accordion with title, tag, difficulty (easy/medium/hard), description, solution, date |
| 📝 **Notes** | Knowledge base | CRUD cards with title, content, source link, date, search/filter |
| 📊 **CV Compare** | CV vs roadmap analysis | Textarea input, keyword matching, gap analysis report |

---

## 🏗️ Proposed Architecture

```text
lib/
├── main.dart
├── app.dart                           // MyCareerApp widget
├── core/
│   ├── constants/
│   │   ├── app_constants.dart         // Storage keys, default data keys
│   │   └── mastery_data.dart          // Static mastery WHY/HOW/DEEP/TEACH data
│   ├── theme/
│   │   ├── app_theme.dart             // Supports multiple themes (Light/Dark extensions)
