## 🎨 Design System & Core Re-use

The app integrates a scalable core architecture (based on the `re-use` folder structure). This entails:
1. **Theming Extensions**: Leveraging `ThemeExtension` to easily inject colors and typography ensuring straightforward multi-theme setup down the line.
2. **Flexible Typography**: Utilizing centralized font families to make design tweaks seamless.
3. **Structured DI**: All external services, use-cases, and cubits registered coherently via `DIHelper`.

---

## 📦 Dependencies Required

```yaml
dependencies:
  flutter:
    sdk: flutter
  flutter_bloc: ^9.0.0
  get_it: ^8.0.0
  go_router: ^17.1.0        # Nested ShellRouting for tabs
  shared_preferences: ^2.5.5
  json_annotation: ^4.9.0
  url_launcher: ^6.3.0
  google_fonts: ^6.2.0

dev_dependencies:
  flutter_test:
    sdk: flutter
  flutter_lints: ^6.0.0
  json_serializable: ^6.9.0
  build_runner: ^2.4.0
```

---

## 🖼️ Assets Required

> [!NOTE]
> We will **not use any internal assets/images**. We will rely entirely on **emojis and first-character initials** for icons/topics (e.g., 📁📋🐙 or 'M' for Mobile). This keeps the app incredibly lightweight without losing visual distinctiveness. System font icons will be used where emojis don't suffice.

---

## 📋 Implementation Tasks (Ordered)

### Phase 1: Core Setup & DI structure
- [ ] **T1.1** — Setup `core/theme/` utilizing the scalable `theme_extension` approach for colors/text mapping CSS variables.
- [ ] **T1.2** — Setup `core/router/` utilizing `GoRouter` with `ShellRoute` setup for tabbed navigation matching the 6 sections.
- [ ] **T1.3** — Implement `core/storage/local_storage_service.dart` wrapper implementation for persistence.
- [ ] **T1.4** — Create `core/constants/mastery_data.dart` holding static JSON representation of mastery rules.
- [ ] **T1.5** — Create `core/di/injection.dart` and `di_helper.dart`.
- [ ] **T1.6** — Initialize base `app.dart` to instantiate Material App and Router.

### Phase 2: Domain Entities
- [ ] **T2.1** — Create entities: `sidebar_link.dart`, `roadmap_section.dart`, `roadmap_item.dart`, `mastery_info.dart`, `book.dart`, `tip.dart`, `problem.dart`, `note.dart`, `cv_analysis_result.dart`.

### Phase 3: Data Layer (Repositories)
- [ ] **T3.1** — Implement `sidebar_repository.dart` to read/write external app links.
- [ ] **T3.2** — Implement `roadmap_repository.dart` for section configurations and completion tracking.
- [ ] **T3.3** — Implement `books_repository.dart`, `tips_repository.dart`, `problems_repository.dart`, `notes_repository.dart` for standard CRUD with SharedPreferences.

### Phase 4: Shared & Form Widgets
- [ ] **T4.1** — Build `app_modal.dart` overlay logic matching web behavior.
- [ ] **T4.2** — Build `app_card.dart` supporting CSS-like hover effects.
- [ ] **T4.3** — Build `app_progress_bar.dart` mapped to gradient progress bar visuals.
- [ ] **T4.4** — Build `app_tag.dart` and `app_legend_pill.dart` colored identifiers.
- [ ] **T4.5** — Build `app_form_field.dart`, `app_danger_button.dart`.

### Phase 5: Navigation Shell (ShellRoute Support)
- [ ] **T5.1** — Build `app_shell.dart` containing `sidebar.dart` and `top_nav_bar.dart` mapped around a `ShellRoute` inner navigation area.
- [ ] **T5.2** — Develop the Sidebar manager logic allowing dynamic URL emoji links editing.

### Phase 6: Roadmap Feature
- [ ] **T6.1** — Setup `roadmap_cubit.dart` managing progression states.
- [ ] **T6.2** — Build `roadmap_page.dart` wiring up grid maps.
- [ ] **T6.3** — Build `section_card.dart` and recursive checkboxes UI (`topic_item.dart`).
- [ ] **T6.4** — Construct the `mastery_modal.dart` implementing the deep dive checklist workflow logic.
- [ ] **T6.5** — Finalize topic and section manager modals for CRUD operations on roadmap data.

### Phase 7: Books Feature
- [ ] **T7.1** — Setup `books_cubit.dart`.
- [ ] **T7.2** — Build `books_page.dart` UI grids.
- [ ] **T7.3** — Implement Add/Edit `book_form_modal.dart`.

### Phase 8: Tips Feature
- [ ] **T8.1** — Setup `tips_cubit.dart`.
- [ ] **T8.2** — Build `tips_page.dart`.
- [ ] **T8.3** — Implement `tip_card.dart` and `tip_form_modal.dart`.

### Phase 9: Problems Feature
- [ ] **T9.1** — Setup `problems_cubit.dart`.
- [ ] **T9.2** — Build `problems_page.dart` allowing collapsible problem descriptions.
- [ ] **T9.3** — Implement `problem_card.dart` dynamically styling border by difficulty.
- [ ] **T9.4** — Implement Add `problem_form_modal.dart`.

### Phase 10: Notes Feature
- [ ] **T10.1** — Setup `notes_cubit.dart`.
- [ ] **T10.2** — Build `notes_page.dart` implementing real-time list filtering from text input.
- [ ] **T10.3** — Implement Add `note_form_modal.dart`.

### Phase 11: CV Compare Feature
- [ ] **T11.1** — Setup `cv_compare_cubit.dart`.
- [ ] **T11.2** — Build `cv_compare_page.dart` split 2-panel architecture.
- [ ] **T11.3** — Implement simple string matching algorithm connecting checked topic models against provided Resume textarea input.
- [ ] **T11.4** — Visual display mapping outputs onto `cv_result_card.dart`.

### Phase 12: Settings Feature
- [ ] **T12.1** — Setup `settings_cubit.dart`.
- [ ] **T12.2** — Implement `settings_modal.dart` managing persistent storage wipe methods per section type.

### Phase 13: GoRouter Wiring & DI Integrations
- [ ] **T13.1** — Verify all repositories and cubits are fully initialized inside `injection.dart` using `di_helper.dart`.
- [ ] **T13.2** — Integrate routing hooks attaching cubit providers to paths within `app_router.dart`.
- [ ] **T13.3** — Complete data hydration checking initial cache load on app start.

### Phase 14: Verification
- [ ] **T14.1** — Test GoRouter deep linking and tab switching.
- [ ] **T14.2** — Verify responsive layout scaling seamlessly eliminating fixed boundaries limits locally.
- [ ] **T14.3** — Comprehensive test execution running `flutter analyze` guaranteeing zero-warn builds.

